Chablis this winter at Sherry’s now that you can choose among those of Simmonet, Pic, and Servin . . . discussing the vine- yards and vintages of Bordeaux with Seymour Weller, an Amer- ican who has headed Chateau Haut Brion for the past decade — I found him a man of infinite charm, wine wisdom, and integrity. No wonder the French have elected him Mayor of a town in Normandy ... more and more do I appreciate the delight of wines such as Chateau de Sancerre and Pouilly Fume

much ruin this year in certain wine sections by freak hail storms. Interesting to see the lookout stations from which rockets are sent into clouds in an effort to change the hail into rain. Over 200 such stations in Burgundy alone . . . wine prices have been going up steadily for months in France. Chateau Mouton Roths- child 1947 now commands 1000 francs the bottle on the Bordeaux market the reunion lunch with Kenneth Dean at Tour d’Argent in Paris enroute back to the shop from a visit to his State Department son in Germany. He was brimming over with un- qualified praise for the 1949 vintage in Rhine and Moselle and comparing it to the great 1921 .. . bouquets to the following great treasures of France which are now at Sherry’s — Chateau Haut Brion 1929, Single Cask Unblended Cognac, Dom Perignon 1921 Champagne, Comte de Moucheron Montrachet 1947, Romanee Conti 1934, Chateau Haut Brion Blane 1947

cheered to see the increased amount of wine being consumed in France this year by my fellow countrymen visiting here this
